<p>
In <a href="[% base_path %]humour/Selina-Mandrake/"><i>Selina Mandrake - The Slayer</i></a>, the titular protagonist (whom I want to be
<a href="[% base_path %]humour/Selina-Mandrake/cast.html#selina">played
by Emma Watson</a>) is able to "kick ass" (or <a
href="https://buffyfanfiction.fandom.com/wiki/Selinaverse#Slaying_in_the_Selinaverse">“slay”
and/or “dispel”</a>) without needing
a wand or any other violent weapon.
</p>

<p>
This captioned image was originally conceived for use in
<a href="[% base_path %]humour/Terminator/Liberation/">a different screenplay</a>
and has later provided inspiration for
<a href="[% base_path %]humour/Selina-Mandrake/ongoing-text.html#the-guide-after-the-three">a
scene in <i>Selina</i></a>.
</p>

<p>
For you people lacking imagination: you can figuratively “kick someone's ass” by
convincing them they had been wrong, or by winning in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chess">Chess</a>,
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Checkers">Checkers</a>,
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bohnanza">Bohnanza</a>,
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Darts">Darts</a>,
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esports">electronic sports</a>,
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basketball">Basketball</a>,
or whatever, or alternatively by enlightening someone.
</p>

<p>
(That put aside, I don't rule out that Emma Watson is a good <a
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts">mixed martial arts</a>
fighter despite appearances to the contrary. Do note that while she might
get angry (which has been erroneously referred to as "verbal violence"), <a
href="[% base_path
%]meta/FAQ/featuring_sexy_women_and_girls.xhtml">she won’t intentionally
attack you out of the blue</a> or even deliberately kick a friendly cat or
dog.)
</p>

