[% BLOCK cast_american_as_a_britishwoman %]

[% WRAPPER github_captioned_image_joke id = "cast_an_American_actress"  header = "“One does not simply cast an American actress for a Britishwoman’s role.”"  repo_href = "http://github.com/shlomif/Captioned-Image-One-does-not-Simply-cast-an-American-Actress"  src = base_path _ "humour/images/one-does-not-simply-cast-an-american-actress.svg.webp"  alt = "“One does not simply cast an American actress for a Britishwoman’s role.”"    %]

[% WRAPPER quote  %]
<p>
“One does not simply cast an American actress for a Britishwoman’s role.”
</p>
[%- END -%]

<p>
This was inspired by a <a href="https://twitter.com/shlomif/status/1174368159060627456">a Twitter conversation</a>
where some people suggested that I should consider casting <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emma_Stone">Emma Stone</a> instead of Emma Watson
for <a href="https://www.shlomifish.org/humour/Selina-Mandrake/cast.html#selina">the role of Selina</a>
in my <a href="https://www.shlomifish.org/humour/Selina-Mandrake/"><i>Selina Mandrake - The Slayer</i></a>
film.
</p>

<p>
It is not quite accurate because Renée Zellweger played Bridget Jones in <a
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bridget_Jones%27s_Diary_(film)"><i>Bridget
Jones’ Diary</i></a>, Anne Hathaway played Jane Austen in <a
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Becoming_Jane"><i>Becoming Jane</i></a>,
Gwyneth Paltrow played an Englishwoman in <a
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shakespeare_in_Love"><i>Shakespeare in
Love</i></a>, and recently Meryl Streep played Margaret Thatcher in <a
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Iron_Lady_%28film%29"><i>The Iron
Lady</i></a>.
</p>

<p>
The real issue is that I believe Emma Watson is the only actress who
can play Selina, and may have kind of modelled and adapted the character of
Selina after her, having deviated from my original concept.
</p>

<p>
<b>Update:</b> being the <q>do and let do</q> proponent that I am, I think
an Emma Stone take on <i>Selina Mandrake - The Slayer</i> (or a <a href="https://twitter.com/shlomif/status/1403524835091812352">Cookie Monster one</a> or whatever)
has a potential to be both different and great.
</p>

[%- END -%]

